main event: Two targets were observed on radar traveling parallel, maintaining a distance of 5-6 miles apart, before disappearing together.
interesting points: The observation lasted 15 minutes, there was an indication of a 'Joining' or 'splitting' maneuver, no contact was made with investigating Airforce aircraft, the targets were possible balloons or aircraft, and multiple witnesses reported seeing two oval shaped discs.
sighted object: two radar targets and two oval shaped discs
witness description: reported seeing two oval shaped discs at night with clear skies and many stars
